1
00:00:06,589 --> 00:00:11,344
All right, that wraps up our talent show
on our final night together.

2
00:00:11,428 --> 00:00:13,888
Up next is the <i>manito </i>reveal.

3
00:00:13,972 --> 00:00:16,975
We'll finish up today's schedule
with that and then head to bed.

4
00:00:17,058 --> 00:00:19,227
- That was fun.
- Thank you.

5
00:00:19,310 --> 00:00:20,854
- Thank you.
- Thank you.

6
00:00:20,937 --> 00:00:22,814
Oh, man, I forgot to bring a card.

7
00:00:22,897 --> 00:00:24,399
I think I have some extra ones, <i>hyung</i>.

8
00:00:24,482 --> 00:00:25,483
- Yeah? Can I have one?
- Sure.

9
00:00:25,567 --> 00:00:27,777
- Here, take one of these three.
- Okay, thank you.

10
00:00:27,861 --> 00:00:28,862
Me too?

11
00:00:28,945 --> 00:00:30,238
"To my <i>manito</i>."

12
00:00:30,321 --> 00:00:32,073
(IRONCLAD DEFENSE)

13
00:00:32,574 --> 00:00:34,617
A CARD TO MY MANITO

14
00:00:34,701 --> 00:00:37,162
It must be one of the people
who made me a <i>ssam </i>earlier.

15
00:00:37,245 --> 00:00:41,082
Yeah, I was thinking it was one of them.
I mean Hye-jeong suddenly just--

16
00:00:41,166 --> 00:00:42,459
Seon-hwa too.

17
00:00:43,293 --> 00:00:44,919
She made me a <i>ssam </i>as well.

18
00:00:45,962 --> 00:00:47,922
To be honest,
that's when I figured it out.

19
00:00:48,006 --> 00:00:49,174
I kind of figured it out too.

20
00:00:49,257 --> 00:00:51,301
Because Seon-hwa
would never make you a <i>ssam</i>.

21
00:00:51,384 --> 00:00:52,635
Why not?

22
00:00:52,719 --> 00:00:55,472
- I mean, she could have.
- Yeah, right. No way.

23
00:00:55,555 --> 00:00:57,182
(UNWAVERING)

24
00:00:57,265 --> 00:00:59,309
- We were writing cards. Here.
- Oh, really?

25
00:00:59,392 --> 00:01:00,685
I should write one too.

26
00:01:03,938 --> 00:01:05,356
- Seon-hwa.
- Yes?

27
00:01:05,440 --> 00:01:06,691
What are you writing?

28
00:01:07,275 --> 00:01:10,653
Uh, I'm writing a long message
for my <i>unni</i>.

29
00:01:11,237 --> 00:01:13,948
- What?
- What? For the <i>unni </i>I'm the <i>manito </i>for.

30
00:01:15,116 --> 00:01:16,451
What are you talking about?

31
00:01:16,534 --> 00:01:18,661
It's someone else.

32
00:01:19,662 --> 00:01:23,249
I just asked what you were writing.
What do you mean "it's someone else"?

33
00:01:24,417 --> 00:01:25,543
Please go away.

34
00:01:25,627 --> 00:01:26,795
- Please go away.
- What?

35
00:01:27,378 --> 00:01:28,880
What's going on with you?

36
00:01:32,467 --> 00:01:35,345
Let's sit in a circle
like before and do the <i>manito </i>reveal.

37
00:01:35,428 --> 00:01:37,055
All right, everyone, gather around.

38
00:01:38,098 --> 00:01:38,932
Oh.

39
00:01:39,015 --> 00:01:40,058
(SEES WOO-SEOK'S GIFT)

40
00:01:40,141 --> 00:01:43,144
- If he's my <i>manito</i>, I'm dead.
- Nice letter, hope it's for me?

41
00:01:43,645 --> 00:01:46,022
- Wow. Seriously.
- Can't I just have it?

42
00:01:46,106 --> 00:01:47,649
- I know.
- I want is so bad.

43
00:01:47,732 --> 00:01:50,443
Aw, he even wrote a card.

44
00:01:50,527 --> 00:01:52,362
I'd do anything to get that.

45
00:01:52,445 --> 00:01:54,823
- You're not getting it.
- Oh, I really want it.

46
00:01:54,906 --> 00:01:57,075
This is great. You're not getting it!

47
00:01:58,618 --> 00:02:01,079
- Serves you right!
- This is awesome!

48
00:02:01,162 --> 00:02:02,997
You're not getting what you want!

49
00:02:04,165 --> 00:02:05,708
- It could be for me.
- Right.

50
00:02:05,792 --> 00:02:07,418
Right. You never know.

51
00:02:07,502 --> 00:02:10,505
- He said I'm right. It's for me.
- Wow. Please.

52
00:02:10,588 --> 00:02:11,756
HEART-POUNDING MANITO REVEAL

53
00:02:11,840 --> 00:02:12,841
All right, then.

54
00:02:12,924 --> 00:02:15,218
Now you can tell us
who you were the <i>manito </i>for.

55
00:02:15,301 --> 00:02:17,929
After you announce it to the circle,
you can give them your gift.

56
00:02:18,012 --> 00:02:21,558
Of course, you didn't know about
the <i>manito </i>when you prepared the gift.

57
00:02:21,641 --> 00:02:24,727
So, please just think of it as fate
and accept it.

58
00:02:24,811 --> 00:02:26,563
Oh, a mosquito.

59
00:02:26,646 --> 00:02:27,647
ACCIDENTALLY SPARKS APPLAUSE

60
00:02:27,730 --> 00:02:29,357
- They're clapping.
- I wasn't clapping.

61
00:02:29,440 --> 00:02:31,109
I was swatting at a mosquito.

62
00:02:31,192 --> 00:02:34,112
- All right, Seon-hwa.
- Oh, so, I…

63
00:02:34,195 --> 00:02:35,947
- Hold on. Let's see who…
- Mmm.

64
00:02:36,030 --> 00:02:38,491
Does anyone think Seon-hwa could be your…

65
00:02:38,575 --> 00:02:41,244
- I mentioned this earlier upstairs, but…
- I was like, "Oh?"

66
00:02:41,327 --> 00:02:43,705
She made him a <i>ssam </i>all of a sudden.
I saw it.

67
00:02:44,581 --> 00:02:45,582
Kwang-soo.

68
00:02:45,665 --> 00:02:47,500
Huh? Oh, thanks.

69
00:02:48,042 --> 00:02:49,711
SHOWED UP AND GAVE HIM A SSAM

70
00:02:49,794 --> 00:02:51,713
- Enjoy.
- Hey, thanks. It's really good.

71
00:02:51,796 --> 00:02:53,131
(WALKS AWAY
WITHOUT LOOKING BACK)

72
00:02:53,214 --> 00:02:54,424
But…

73
00:02:55,049 --> 00:02:56,426
up until then,

74
00:02:57,218 --> 00:02:58,928
she'd only been talking to Woo-seok.

75
00:03:00,430 --> 00:03:02,765
I thought it was for him,
but she gave it to me.

76
00:03:03,308 --> 00:03:05,935
Well, if I'm wrong, I'd appreciate it.

77
00:03:06,019 --> 00:03:10,064
But if I'm right, I wouldn't exactly
be happy about it. I mean…

78
00:03:10,148 --> 00:03:12,066
Yeah, I've got mixed feelings right now.

79
00:03:12,150 --> 00:03:13,401
- Well, we don't know yet.
- Right.

80
00:03:13,484 --> 00:03:15,069
- You were working so hard…
- That's nice.

81
00:03:15,153 --> 00:03:17,280
- …so that's why I gave it to you.
- That's what I thought.

82
00:03:17,363 --> 00:03:20,074
- So, Seon-hwa, who's your <i>manito</i>?
- My <i>manito </i>is…

83
00:03:20,158 --> 00:03:21,284
Is it Kwang-soo?

84
00:03:22,744 --> 00:03:24,621
CHIEF YU?

85
00:03:25,205 --> 00:03:26,623
REALLY?

86
00:03:27,790 --> 00:03:30,793
Is it Jae-seok?

87
00:03:30,877 --> 00:03:31,711
Me?

88
00:03:32,253 --> 00:03:33,546
Is it Jae-seok?

89
00:03:33,630 --> 00:03:35,548
- It's Kwang-soo.
- Oh, you surprised me.

90
00:03:35,632 --> 00:03:38,343
Come on, what are you doing?
What's the matter with her?

91
00:03:38,426 --> 00:03:42,013
I mean, what's the matter with her?

92
00:03:42,096 --> 00:03:45,683
- So that's why you fed me?
- Yeah, I'm sorry.

93
00:03:46,559 --> 00:03:48,061
(I SEE…)

94
00:03:48,144 --> 00:03:49,729
- That's right.
- Thanks.

95
00:03:50,730 --> 00:03:52,023
"That's right."

96
00:03:52,106 --> 00:03:55,235
I knew it.
She gave him a <i>ssam </i>out of nowhere.

97
00:03:55,318 --> 00:03:56,527
Whoa!

98
00:03:56,611 --> 00:04:00,573
- Wow. That's so pretty.
- I love this kind of thing. Whoa!

99
00:04:00,657 --> 00:04:02,700
- And it plays a carol too.
- He's into this stuff.

100
00:04:02,784 --> 00:04:05,870
- Oh, really? I'm glad.
- I really am. Thanks. Whoa.

101
00:04:06,579 --> 00:04:08,915
She even wrote him a card
with a long message.

102
00:04:08,998 --> 00:04:11,000
"To my personal jester, Kwang-soo.

103
00:04:11,084 --> 00:04:14,504
Kwang-soo, I was torn between
joining your team and Woo-seok's.

104
00:04:14,587 --> 00:04:18,466
Even though I ended up making
the decision not to choose your team…"

105
00:04:19,634 --> 00:04:22,095
"…I've always been a big fan of yours.

106
00:04:22,762 --> 00:04:25,139
I'd only seen you on TV,
but you're even funnier live.

107
00:04:25,223 --> 00:04:27,141
- You had me laughing all day."
- Oh, that's nice.

108
00:04:27,225 --> 00:04:29,102
"Behind the jokes, there's such kindness.

109
00:04:29,185 --> 00:04:31,396
Your wit and sense of humor
are one of a kind."

110
00:04:31,479 --> 00:04:33,564
- It's all about how funny he is.
- "Thank you so much for always

111
00:04:33,648 --> 00:04:35,191
working so hard for us, to make us laugh.

112
00:04:35,275 --> 00:04:38,236
I'll remember these moments
for the rest of my life."

113
00:04:38,319 --> 00:04:39,779
FUNNY KWANG-SOO

114
00:04:39,862 --> 00:04:44,575
All right, well, does anyone think
Kwang-soo might be your <i>manito</i>?

115
00:04:46,035 --> 00:04:47,078
Anyone?

116
00:04:48,371 --> 00:04:49,956
ME?

117
00:04:51,124 --> 00:04:52,959
Hey, why are you looking at him like that?

118
00:04:53,042 --> 00:04:55,378
No, I was just wondering
if he really hadn't noticed.

119
00:04:55,962 --> 00:04:57,463
It's not me.

120
00:04:57,547 --> 00:04:58,673
It's you.

121
00:04:58,756 --> 00:04:59,924
- No way.
- It's a face-off.

122
00:05:00,008 --> 00:05:01,217
- He said no.
- "No way."

123
00:05:01,301 --> 00:05:02,719
- Yes way.
- It's not.

124
00:05:02,802 --> 00:05:03,720
"No way."

125
00:05:04,304 --> 00:05:05,847
- Who is it?
- It's Lee-joong.

126
00:05:05,930 --> 00:05:07,307
It is Lee-joong?

127
00:05:07,890 --> 00:05:09,809
Really? Oh, really?

128
00:05:09,892 --> 00:05:12,061
But if it's him, why's he saying it's not?

129
00:05:12,145 --> 00:05:13,062
I don't know.

130
00:05:13,146 --> 00:05:15,273
- Lee-joong, didn't you notice anything?
- Here. Take this.

131
00:05:15,356 --> 00:05:18,401
- No.
- But Kwang-soo, what did you do for him?

132
00:05:19,360 --> 00:05:23,281
First of all, earlier,
when we were all dancing together,

133
00:05:23,364 --> 00:05:25,450
- I kept shouting out his name.
- Right.

134
00:05:25,533 --> 00:05:26,534
Come on, Lee-joong!

135
00:05:26,617 --> 00:05:27,577
2 HOURS EARLIER

136
00:05:27,660 --> 00:05:28,661
Here we go!

137
00:05:28,745 --> 00:05:32,874
- Yeah! Yoon Lee-joong!
- Yeah!

138
00:05:32,957 --> 00:05:35,126
- I can't do it.
- Yoon Lee-joong!

139
00:05:35,209 --> 00:05:37,295
Shake it! Shake it like crazy.

140
00:05:37,378 --> 00:05:38,713
- Remember?
- Right.

141
00:05:38,796 --> 00:05:41,591
And, when we passed each other
in the dining area,

142
00:05:41,674 --> 00:05:45,011
I said a few nice things.

143
00:05:45,094 --> 00:05:47,305
- Did you notice that?
- No.

144
00:05:47,388 --> 00:05:50,183
Open it.

145
00:05:50,266 --> 00:05:52,477
(THIS IS HILARIOUS)

146
00:05:52,560 --> 00:05:53,895
What is it?

147
00:05:55,229 --> 00:05:58,232
- Is that how people normally open gifts?
- Right?

148
00:05:58,816 --> 00:06:00,109
KWANG-SOO'S GIFT A POWER BANK

149
00:06:00,193 --> 00:06:02,362
- That's cute.
- Oh, that's nice.

150
00:06:02,445 --> 00:06:04,489
All right, Lee-joong.
Read a little for us.

151
00:06:04,572 --> 00:06:06,366
- Okay. Whoa!
- Whoa.

152
00:06:07,742 --> 00:06:12,372
"When you said you didn't want to play
any games or sleep outdoors,

153
00:06:12,455 --> 00:06:16,125
I remember thinking to myself,
'Why is he like that?'

154
00:06:17,126 --> 00:06:20,546
I wish that we had had
more chances to talk.

155
00:06:20,630 --> 00:06:22,757
As you work as a correctional officer,
you could charge your phone"…

156
00:06:22,840 --> 00:06:24,008
Wait, you can't just skip ahead.

157
00:06:24,092 --> 00:06:25,093
- Read the middle.
- Why not?

158
00:06:25,176 --> 00:06:27,970
Otherwise it sounds like I thought
that about you and that was it!

159
00:06:28,054 --> 00:06:29,597
You have to read the part in between.

160
00:06:29,680 --> 00:06:31,974
- He said to read a little bit.
- Yeah. Just a little.

161
00:06:32,058 --> 00:06:34,227
- I know he said that, but still.
- There's a middle part?

162
00:06:34,310 --> 00:06:36,437
THE MOMENTS TOGETHER
AND OUR CHATS TAUGHT ME…

163
00:06:36,521 --> 00:06:37,563
I HOPED THE B&B COULD…

164
00:06:37,647 --> 00:06:39,315
IMPORTANT PART SKIPPED

165
00:06:39,399 --> 00:06:42,318
- The important part is right after that.
- Read the middle too? Okay.

166
00:06:42,402 --> 00:06:44,487
"After getting to know you
and talking with you,

167
00:06:44,570 --> 00:06:46,697
I realized you're tough on the outside

168
00:06:46,781 --> 00:06:49,492
but actually warm at heart
and really thoughtful.

169
00:06:49,575 --> 00:06:54,997
I came to understand that wanting
to just rest and do nothing is something

170
00:06:55,081 --> 00:06:57,708
that only people who live intense,
passionate lives can say.

171
00:06:57,792 --> 00:07:00,503
I regret that I might not have done
everything I could

172
00:07:00,586 --> 00:07:03,673
to make things as fun or relaxing
for you as I'd hoped.

173
00:07:03,756 --> 00:07:06,968
Please stay healthy,
and always remember these moments."

174
00:07:10,096 --> 00:07:14,392
Honestly, Lee-joong was probably
the person I least wanted to pick.

175
00:07:14,475 --> 00:07:17,186
He speaks bluntly,
and he can come off a bit rough.

176
00:07:17,270 --> 00:07:20,231
He seemed kind of intimidating,
so it was hard to approach him.

177
00:07:20,314 --> 00:07:22,150
- It was fun.
- I'm so glad.

178
00:07:22,233 --> 00:07:23,359
I'm happy to see you smile.

179
00:07:23,443 --> 00:07:24,735
I'm glad you're feeling better.

180
00:07:24,819 --> 00:07:26,988
But I ended up becoming his <i>manito</i>,

181
00:07:27,071 --> 00:07:30,908
and as I talked to him
and got to spend more time with him,

182
00:07:30,992 --> 00:07:33,786
I realized that in reality
he's actually very expressive.

183
00:07:33,870 --> 00:07:35,663
I was really grateful for that.

184
00:07:36,164 --> 00:07:38,082
All right, now, Kwang-chul.

185
00:07:38,166 --> 00:07:39,876
- Okay, I'll tell.
- Who is it?

186
00:07:39,959 --> 00:07:42,712
- It's Mr. Yu Jae-seok.
- Oh, it's me?

187
00:07:42,795 --> 00:07:44,464
- I kind of knew it actually.
- Really?

188
00:07:44,547 --> 00:07:46,340
- I had a feeling it was Jae-seok.
- Really?

189
00:07:46,424 --> 00:07:49,010
- Wow! That's a pretty lamp.
- Oh!

190
00:07:49,093 --> 00:07:51,345
- Autumn is reading season.
- It's cute.

191
00:07:51,429 --> 00:07:53,222
- This is a big coincidence.
- Why?

192
00:07:53,306 --> 00:07:54,557
Well, uh, Chae-eun is my…

193
00:07:54,640 --> 00:07:56,434
JAE-SEOK WAS KWANG-CHUL'S
DAUGHTER CHAE-EUN'S MANITO

194
00:07:56,517 --> 00:07:59,270
- I got a gift from Dad. Now…
- Oh, wow. The whole family.

195
00:07:59,353 --> 00:08:01,063
- It's a beanie.
- Oh, I love it.

196
00:08:01,147 --> 00:08:02,940
- Yeah, you like it?
- I do, thank you.

197
00:08:03,024 --> 00:08:04,775
What a coincidence.
I got a gift from her dad.

198
00:08:04,859 --> 00:08:05,693
That's right.

199
00:08:05,776 --> 00:08:08,821
And now I'm giving one to his daughter.
This is amazing.

200
00:08:09,530 --> 00:08:11,407
"To my <i>manito </i>Chae-eun.

201
00:08:11,491 --> 00:08:14,327
I really hope
your precious dream comes true.

202
00:08:14,410 --> 00:08:16,704
- It was truly so wonderful for me…"
- Why's she crying?

203
00:08:16,787 --> 00:08:18,456
- "…to hear that you want to follow…"
- Hold on.

204
00:08:18,539 --> 00:08:22,001
"…in your dad's footsteps
and pursue law enforcement.

205
00:08:22,084 --> 00:08:24,504
- Just like your amazing dad…"
- Why's this making me cry?

206
00:08:24,587 --> 00:08:27,340
- "…who keeps everyone of us safe…"
- Wait, now Kwang-chul's crying?

207
00:08:28,466 --> 00:08:31,552
"…I hope you grow up to be someone
who protects the lives and safety

208
00:08:31,636 --> 00:08:32,929
of many people, Chae-eun.

209
00:08:33,012 --> 00:08:34,555
From Yu Jae-seok."

210
00:08:34,639 --> 00:08:36,057
CHOKED UP BY ENCOURAGING MESSAGE

211
00:08:36,140 --> 00:08:38,643
- Oh, stop crying.
- What are you both crying for?

212
00:08:38,726 --> 00:08:41,437
- I'm just so happy. That's why.
- Oh, you're happy.

213
00:08:42,021 --> 00:08:43,439
What a coincidence.

214
00:08:43,773 --> 00:08:45,066
(KWANG-SOO GRABS TISSUE)

215
00:08:45,149 --> 00:08:46,651
I'm really glad though.

216
00:08:47,193 --> 00:08:50,321
Kwang-chul gave me a gift,
and I gave one to Chae-eun.

217
00:08:50,404 --> 00:08:51,405
This is so meaningful.

218
00:08:51,489 --> 00:08:54,158
This is such a meaningful gift. Thank you.

219
00:08:54,242 --> 00:08:56,744
When I heard that Chae-eun was taking
the CSAT in a week…

220
00:08:56,827 --> 00:08:57,828
Yeah.

221
00:08:57,912 --> 00:09:00,748
…I know her dad said
this experience mattered more,

222
00:09:00,831 --> 00:09:03,459
but I still couldn't help worrying,
being a father myself.

223
00:09:03,543 --> 00:09:06,087
Regardless, I'm sure Chae-eun knows
what's best for her.

224
00:09:06,170 --> 00:09:09,632
I wrote the card hoping she grows up
to become a great police officer.

225
00:09:09,715 --> 00:09:12,260
- Thank you.
- I'm really glad it worked out like this.

226
00:09:12,343 --> 00:09:13,719
Okay, who's next?

227
00:09:13,803 --> 00:09:15,972
Nam-jin, you're the <i>manito </i>for…

228
00:09:16,055 --> 00:09:16,889
Me.

229
00:09:16,973 --> 00:09:18,933
Ye-eun thinks you're her <i>manito</i>.

230
00:09:19,016 --> 00:09:21,018
- Ye-eun is right. It is her.
- Wow!

231
00:09:21,102 --> 00:09:23,020
Wow, that's amazing.

232
00:09:23,104 --> 00:09:26,274
- Yeah, that's nice.
- Oh, how cute! Great hat.

233
00:09:29,026 --> 00:09:31,153
All right, Ye-eun. Your turn.

234
00:09:31,237 --> 00:09:33,823
Nam-soon.

235
00:09:33,906 --> 00:09:35,241
Whoa!

236
00:09:35,324 --> 00:09:38,369
- Whoa, what?
- Who knew it'd turn out like this?

237
00:09:38,452 --> 00:09:40,162
You're completing the brother triangle!

238
00:09:40,246 --> 00:09:41,872
- Yeah, I know.
- That's right.

239
00:09:41,956 --> 00:09:43,416
- For Christmas?
- It's a snow globe.

240
00:09:43,499 --> 00:09:45,167
Oh, a snow globe? Wow.

241
00:09:45,251 --> 00:09:46,836
The gifts are going to the right people.

242
00:09:46,919 --> 00:09:48,754
- Yeah, they are.
- You're right. It's working out.

243
00:09:48,838 --> 00:09:50,840
Honestly, living in today's world,

244
00:09:50,923 --> 00:09:53,759
- it feels like everyone is self-involved.
- Ow, that hurts.

245
00:09:53,843 --> 00:09:55,803
It's rare to have someone step up
and look out for you.

246
00:09:55,886 --> 00:09:57,346
- Can I help?
- You're my <i>manito</i>, aren't you?

247
00:09:57,430 --> 00:09:58,264
No.

248
00:09:58,347 --> 00:10:00,474
- Yeah.
- Through this whole <i>manito </i>thing,

249
00:10:00,558 --> 00:10:04,562
I realized that helping someone out
like this can be really fulfilling.

250
00:10:04,645 --> 00:10:06,063
It made me realize

251
00:10:06,147 --> 00:10:09,317
that looking out for someone
is much harder than I thought.

252
00:10:10,026 --> 00:10:11,694
It also made me feel grateful again

253
00:10:11,777 --> 00:10:14,572
to all the people
who have always looked out for me.

254
00:10:14,655 --> 00:10:15,656
Me?

255
00:10:16,157 --> 00:10:17,867
- It's Seung-jun.
- Oh…

256
00:10:17,950 --> 00:10:19,368
Oh, lucky him.

257
00:10:19,452 --> 00:10:20,536
I'm jealous.

258
00:10:20,620 --> 00:10:23,080
- He said so many nice things to me.
- Oh, did he?

259
00:10:23,164 --> 00:10:24,290
All right, everyone.

260
00:10:24,373 --> 00:10:27,335
Let's give each other a round of applause
for these thoughtful gifts.

261
00:10:29,503 --> 00:10:31,172
Now, about tomorrow morning.

262
00:10:31,255 --> 00:10:32,506
How does 8:00 a.m. sound?

263
00:10:32,590 --> 00:10:34,133
- Sounds good.
- Okay.

264
00:10:34,216 --> 00:10:35,718
You know what's amazing?

265
00:10:35,801 --> 00:10:40,056
The character I'm playing in the project
I'm filming right now is Prince I-an.

266
00:10:40,139 --> 00:10:41,932
Oh, no way. And I-an had you.

267
00:10:42,016 --> 00:10:43,809
- She had me.
- His character's name is I-an.

268
00:10:43,893 --> 00:10:45,770
- It's the same name. Prince I-an.
- Really?

269
00:10:45,853 --> 00:10:48,105
Well "Prince I-an" is…
His actual name is Lee Wan.

270
00:10:48,189 --> 00:10:49,273
Oh, Lee Wan?

271
00:10:49,357 --> 00:10:51,609
- His pen name is Prince I-an.
- Oh, really?

272
00:10:51,692 --> 00:10:53,361
- Gosh, it's an honor.
- It's amazing.

273
00:10:53,444 --> 00:10:54,445
What a coincidence.

274
00:10:54,528 --> 00:10:55,863
- Exactly.
- That's amazing.

275
00:10:55,946 --> 00:10:57,448
Great to do this with family.

276
00:10:57,531 --> 00:10:59,950
- Thank you so much for this.
- My pleasure.

277
00:11:00,034 --> 00:11:01,994
- You and the two brothers.
- Exactly.

278
00:11:02,078 --> 00:11:04,080
- Kwang-soo, let's go wash up.
- Okay.

279
00:11:04,163 --> 00:11:05,748
Good night. See you tomorrow.

280
00:11:05,831 --> 00:11:07,958
- Nam-soon, good night.
- Oh, good night!

281
00:11:08,042 --> 00:11:09,460
- Nam-jin. Good night.
- Good night.

282
00:11:09,543 --> 00:11:10,544
STAFF OFF DUTY

283
00:11:10,628 --> 00:11:12,630
We said we'd pick it up at 7:30, right?

284
00:11:12,713 --> 00:11:13,547
Yeah.

285
00:11:14,048 --> 00:11:17,677
Okay. Gosh, Kwang-soo.
We should go wash up and go to bed now.

286
00:11:18,427 --> 00:11:20,846
- It's really ending.
- I know.

287
00:11:21,347 --> 00:11:24,183
- After breakfast tomorrow…
- After breakfast, it's over.

288
00:11:25,226 --> 00:11:27,937
THE STAFF HEADS TO THE SHOWERS

289
00:11:28,521 --> 00:11:29,730
I'm kind of sad it's ending.

290
00:11:29,814 --> 00:11:31,023
- It's already over?
- Mmm.

291
00:11:31,107 --> 00:11:33,150
I'm tired
but I still don't want it to end.

292
00:11:33,234 --> 00:11:36,237
I mean, it guess it is almost 10:00.

293
00:11:36,779 --> 00:11:37,947
Is it past 10:00?

294
00:11:38,030 --> 00:11:40,157
- Actually, it's 11:00. It's crazy.
- It's 11:00?

295
00:11:40,241 --> 00:11:43,119
- Man. No way.
- Wow.

296
00:11:43,202 --> 00:11:46,789
- It's already our last night.
- No way. I don't wanna go home.

297
00:11:46,872 --> 00:11:48,290
I'm not going to sleep.

298
00:11:48,999 --> 00:11:50,167
- Hey.
- Are you gonna shower?

299
00:11:50,251 --> 00:11:51,085
Yeah, we should.

300
00:11:55,047 --> 00:11:59,301
BITTERSWEET LAST NIGHT

301
00:11:59,802 --> 00:12:02,430
CHIEF YU'S THE FIRST ONE BACK
FROM SHOWERING

302
00:12:05,766 --> 00:12:06,684
SIGHING

303
00:12:07,560 --> 00:12:08,477
GROANING

304
00:12:09,812 --> 00:12:12,565
THE FINAL NIGHT'S FILLED
WITH GROANS

305
00:12:12,940 --> 00:12:14,775
YE-EUN TURNS OFF THE LIGHTS
INSTEAD OF CHIEF YU

306
00:12:18,487 --> 00:12:21,907
THE MOON RISES ONE LAST TIME
AT JAE-SEOK'S B&B

307
00:12:22,283 --> 00:12:24,869
THE DOOR BROTHERS RETURN LATE
FROM SHOWERING

308
00:12:25,619 --> 00:12:26,912
TIPTOEING

309
00:12:26,996 --> 00:12:28,330
CREAK

310
00:12:29,039 --> 00:12:29,999
PAUSE

311
00:12:30,082 --> 00:12:31,333
ZZZ

312
00:12:33,043 --> 00:12:34,378
CREAK

313
00:12:35,045 --> 00:12:36,380
(BROKEN)

314
00:12:36,922 --> 00:12:39,759
LAUGHING

315
00:12:40,843 --> 00:12:44,346
FORTUNATELY,
CHIEF YU'S SOUND ASLEEP

316
00:12:44,430 --> 00:12:46,348
- Wow, you guys can really eat.
- Oh, hi.

317
00:12:46,432 --> 00:12:47,683
GUESTS HOLDING ON
TO THE LAST NIGHT

318
00:12:47,767 --> 00:12:49,727
I saw some electric blankets over there.

319
00:12:49,810 --> 00:12:51,228
Nam-jin, did you eat?

320
00:12:51,312 --> 00:12:54,440
I used to eat two or three bowls of rice
at every meal.

321
00:12:54,523 --> 00:12:57,693
How are you so thin? Metabolism?

322
00:12:57,777 --> 00:12:59,528
Ever since my wife passed away,

323
00:12:59,612 --> 00:13:01,572
- I haven't had much of an appetite.
- Oh.

324
00:13:01,655 --> 00:13:03,032
- Man, I think I'd be the same.
- Right.

325
00:13:03,115 --> 00:13:05,075
I can totally understand
how hard that must be.

326
00:13:05,159 --> 00:13:06,494
I didn't know you'd been through that.

327
00:13:06,577 --> 00:13:08,162
- I'm going to start crying again.
- I saw you.

328
00:13:08,245 --> 00:13:10,039
- I can't look at you.
- When I was holding the mic

329
00:13:10,122 --> 00:13:11,749
- and talking, I was nervous.
- I could see that. Yeah, I…

330
00:13:11,832 --> 00:13:14,877
Then I saw you crying.
It just caught my eye.

331
00:13:14,960 --> 00:13:16,295
I'm just soft-hearted.

332
00:13:16,378 --> 00:13:17,546
Has it been long?

333
00:13:18,088 --> 00:13:20,716
- It happened last September…
- Oh, that must've been so hard.

334
00:13:20,800 --> 00:13:22,968
…so it's been a little over a year
at this point.

335
00:13:23,052 --> 00:13:24,386
I just…

336
00:13:24,470 --> 00:13:26,764
- I just miss her all the time…
- Of course.

337
00:13:26,847 --> 00:13:29,308
- It'd drive anyone crazy.
- …and that's the hardest part, you know?

338
00:13:29,391 --> 00:13:31,602
But you get hurt sometimes, don't you?

339
00:13:31,685 --> 00:13:34,355
We do. Someone actually bit me here once.

340
00:13:34,438 --> 00:13:35,773
- Bit you?
- We get bitten.

341
00:13:35,856 --> 00:13:38,317
- They don't have weapons?
- No, that doesn't happen.

342
00:13:38,400 --> 00:13:40,236
So you just punch them and knock them out?

343
00:13:40,319 --> 00:13:41,529
No, we can't punch them.

344
00:13:41,612 --> 00:13:43,697
Even if they punch us,
we're not allowed to punch them back.

345
00:13:43,781 --> 00:13:46,742
Oh, so you just, like…
You can only hold them back?

346
00:13:46,826 --> 00:13:49,203
- That's right. We just restrain them.
- You just…

347
00:13:49,286 --> 00:13:52,331
- Have you ever had to use a Taser?
- I thought I knew who my <i>manito </i>was,

348
00:13:52,414 --> 00:13:53,415
but now I'm not sure.

349
00:13:53,499 --> 00:13:56,252
Do you have to go out with someone
for them to be your first love?

350
00:13:56,335 --> 00:13:59,296
It's the person that comes to mind
when you think of your first love.

351
00:13:59,380 --> 00:14:00,798
Bryan, do you have a girlfriend?

352
00:14:00,881 --> 00:14:02,800
We can't bring ourself to call it a night

353
00:14:02,883 --> 00:14:05,135
- because we don't want it to end.
- Exactly.

354
00:14:10,641 --> 00:14:14,228
WITH A BLARING ALARM

355
00:14:14,895 --> 00:14:15,896
STAFF QUARTERS 6 A.M.

356
00:14:15,980 --> 00:14:18,274
All right. Today, we don't have to change.

357
00:14:18,357 --> 00:14:19,692
THE DOOR BROTHERS ARE UP EARLY

358
00:14:20,985 --> 00:14:24,196
OFF TO THE SHOWERS FIRST

359
00:14:24,655 --> 00:14:25,656
CHIEF YU IS UP

360
00:14:25,739 --> 00:14:27,324
STAGGERING

361
00:14:27,783 --> 00:14:29,577
STRAIGHT TO THE SINK
AS SOON AS HE WAKES UP

362
00:14:34,999 --> 00:14:37,751
WASHING HIS HAIR
IN THE SINK AGAIN

363
00:14:44,383 --> 00:14:46,927
READY FOR HIS LAST DAY OF WORK

364
00:14:47,011 --> 00:14:47,928
Oh!

365
00:14:48,012 --> 00:14:49,847
- Hello.
- Hye-jeong, good morning.

366
00:14:49,930 --> 00:14:52,766
I wrote this yesterday.

367
00:14:53,309 --> 00:14:54,810
- What's this?
- It's a letter.

368
00:14:55,394 --> 00:14:56,604
You didn't have to…

369
00:14:56,687 --> 00:14:59,273
- No, I wrote one for each of you here.
- Oh. Well, to be honest,

370
00:14:59,356 --> 00:15:01,525
I would've been more touched
if you'd only written one for me.

371
00:15:01,609 --> 00:15:04,278
These are nothing. Just scraps.

372
00:15:04,361 --> 00:15:06,280
- Hye-jeong, thank you.
- Sure.

373
00:15:08,490 --> 00:15:09,617
Seon-hwa!

374
00:15:10,409 --> 00:15:11,619
Good morning.

375
00:15:11,702 --> 00:15:14,079
- I didn't wanna go home.
- Yeah?

376
00:15:14,163 --> 00:15:15,664
I cried in the shower.

377
00:15:15,748 --> 00:15:17,625
Oh, really? Why?

378
00:15:17,708 --> 00:15:20,794
We've got to dance "To You." This thing.

379
00:15:20,878 --> 00:15:23,464
Yeah, we've got to…
We've got to dance together.

380
00:15:23,964 --> 00:15:25,257
Whoa, you're good.

381
00:15:25,341 --> 00:15:28,886
I honestly don't think I'll ever be able
to forget this place.

382
00:15:28,969 --> 00:15:30,471
Yeah, I know. We feel the same.

383
00:15:30,554 --> 00:15:31,722
It's so special.

384
00:15:31,805 --> 00:15:33,349
When we go home,
it kind of lingers with us.

385
00:15:33,432 --> 00:15:34,767
I think it will for me too.

386
00:15:35,225 --> 00:15:38,228
AFTER MORNING GREETINGS,
OFF TO WORK

387
00:15:39,104 --> 00:15:40,898
Is he gonna start the rice?

388
00:15:42,358 --> 00:15:44,401
- <i>Hyung.</i>
- You're here.

389
00:15:44,485 --> 00:15:45,819
Should we go?

390
00:15:46,528 --> 00:15:49,573
I'll do this. You guys should go.
All I need to do is make rice.

391
00:15:50,282 --> 00:15:51,992
You've gotta get going
if you wanna make it.

392
00:15:52,076 --> 00:15:53,369
- Okay.
- We'll be back.

393
00:15:53,452 --> 00:15:54,870
- All right, see you later.
- Yeah.

394
00:15:55,663 --> 00:15:57,665
Pick up at 7:30, right?

395
00:15:58,791 --> 00:16:00,125
Fresh gomtang!

396
00:16:00,209 --> 00:16:01,210
I know.

397
00:16:01,835 --> 00:16:04,546
Of all the dishes we had here,
which was your favorite?

398
00:16:05,130 --> 00:16:06,590
The doenjang soup.

399
00:16:06,674 --> 00:16:09,343
I mixed rice into it
and had it with kimchi.

400
00:16:09,843 --> 00:16:13,097
- That sounds so good.
- But you had to have it with kimchi.

401
00:16:15,349 --> 00:16:17,643
- Hello.
- Hello.

402
00:16:17,726 --> 00:16:19,979
This isn't going to spill, right?

403
00:16:20,062 --> 00:16:22,314
PICKING UP THE POT, THEY LEFT

404
00:16:23,023 --> 00:16:26,110
WITH THE TAPE
AND PLASTIC THEY BROUGHT

405
00:16:26,402 --> 00:16:28,070
SEALED TIGHT

406
00:16:28,153 --> 00:16:28,988
There.

407
00:16:29,071 --> 00:16:31,323
- You have a driver's license, right?
- Yeah.

408
00:16:31,407 --> 00:16:34,410
So when we go to the car why do you
always go to the passenger seat?

409
00:16:34,493 --> 00:16:36,954
No, it's just that you got in
the driver's seat first

410
00:16:37,037 --> 00:16:38,038
when we drove here.

411
00:16:38,122 --> 00:16:41,208
Yeah, but you could've said,
"I'll drive" or something.

412
00:16:41,291 --> 00:16:43,419
- Do you want me to?
- Would you?

413
00:16:43,502 --> 00:16:44,962
- No.
- Why not?

414
00:16:46,380 --> 00:16:49,425
Rock-paper-scissors?
Rock, paper, scissors. Shoot.

415
00:16:49,508 --> 00:16:50,676
(SCISSORS) - (PAPER)

416
00:16:53,554 --> 00:16:55,097
It's not gonna spill, right?

417
00:16:55,180 --> 00:16:56,849
There are so many speed bumps.

418
00:16:57,349 --> 00:16:58,934
- Wait a minute.
- Huh?

419
00:16:59,018 --> 00:17:01,395
Did you ask me to drive
so you wouldn't spill it?

420
00:17:01,478 --> 00:17:03,522
- No, no. No, you know…
- Because you were afraid?

421
00:17:03,605 --> 00:17:05,232
- It doesn't matter who spills it.
- Hold on…

422
00:17:05,315 --> 00:17:08,110
Here I thought you just wanted to relax
instead of drive.

423
00:17:08,193 --> 00:17:09,111
No, no.

424
00:17:09,194 --> 00:17:10,988
You're worried
you'll take the blame if it spills.

425
00:17:11,071 --> 00:17:12,072
No, that's not it either.

426
00:17:13,699 --> 00:17:15,951
Wow, this is so good. Want a sip?

427
00:17:16,035 --> 00:17:17,828
- What is it?
- It's good, right?

428
00:17:17,911 --> 00:17:19,538
(DRINKING ALL
OF WOO-SEOK'S COFFEE)

429
00:17:25,085 --> 00:17:26,295
I'm so happy right now.

430
00:17:26,378 --> 00:17:27,629
I've changed my mind.

431
00:17:27,713 --> 00:17:30,507
The best thing I've had here
isn't actually the doenjang soup.

432
00:17:30,591 --> 00:17:31,592
It's that.

433
00:17:35,179 --> 00:17:37,014
I think this should be enough.

434
00:17:39,933 --> 00:17:42,644
CHIEF YU'S MAKING RICE

435
00:17:44,813 --> 00:17:46,273
(COOKING)

436
00:17:46,356 --> 00:17:48,734
- Hey, good morning.
- Good morning.

437
00:17:48,817 --> 00:17:49,651
- Hi.
- Good morning.

438
00:17:49,735 --> 00:17:50,736
Chae-eun, you're up too.

439
00:17:50,819 --> 00:17:52,446
- Yeah.
- Can I help?

440
00:17:52,529 --> 00:17:54,073
The <i>manito's </i>over.

441
00:17:54,156 --> 00:17:55,616
Oh, right.

442
00:17:56,408 --> 00:17:58,202
- Did you sleep well?
- Yeah, I did.

443
00:17:58,285 --> 00:17:59,912
- Oh, really?
- I slept better on the second night.

444
00:17:59,995 --> 00:18:00,996
- Right, yeah.
- Yeah.

445
00:18:01,080 --> 00:18:04,333
I think my kids and I actually
slept better here than we usually do.

446
00:18:04,416 --> 00:18:05,793
- Oh, really?
- Yeah.

447
00:18:05,876 --> 00:18:08,087
It's strange. I wish I could stay longer.

448
00:18:08,170 --> 00:18:10,255
Right. You're back to work Monday, right?

449
00:18:10,339 --> 00:18:11,423
Yeah, Monday.

450
00:18:11,507 --> 00:18:14,384
I've actually got a very important
promotion test next week

451
00:18:14,468 --> 00:18:15,594
that I'm prepping for.

452
00:18:15,677 --> 00:18:17,930
- Oh.
- So I've been keeping in shape.

453
00:18:18,305 --> 00:18:21,016
JAE-SEOK'S B&B TOOK PRIORITY
OVER THE CSAT AND PROMOTION TEST

454
00:18:21,100 --> 00:18:22,392
They're back.

455
00:18:22,476 --> 00:18:24,478
- Oh.
- They're back from an errand.

456
00:18:24,561 --> 00:18:26,230
Okay, gomtang.

457
00:18:26,313 --> 00:18:27,731
THE GOMTANG HAS ARRIVED

458
00:18:27,815 --> 00:18:29,233
It makes for a hearty breakfast.

459
00:18:29,316 --> 00:18:30,609
HEARTY GOMTANG
FOR THEIR FINAL MORNING

460
00:18:30,692 --> 00:18:32,986
Perfect timing.
The rice is starting to steam.

461
00:18:33,070 --> 00:18:34,279
One, two, three.

462
00:18:36,281 --> 00:18:38,158
Kwang-chul's got
a promotion test coming up.

463
00:18:38,242 --> 00:18:39,076
When?

464
00:18:39,159 --> 00:18:40,410
- Next week.
- Whoa.

465
00:18:40,494 --> 00:18:43,163
Chae-eun's got the CSAT,
and he's got a promotion test.

466
00:18:43,247 --> 00:18:45,457
What about you, Chae-won?
Do you have anything coming up?

467
00:18:45,541 --> 00:18:47,209
No, that's why I wanna stay.

468
00:18:48,961 --> 00:18:50,212
She wants to stay longer?

469
00:18:50,295 --> 00:18:52,005
Chae-won, I'm so glad you like it here.

470
00:18:52,089 --> 00:18:54,383
Seon-hwa said
she cried in the shower last night

471
00:18:54,466 --> 00:18:56,009
because she was so sad to leave.

472
00:18:56,093 --> 00:18:58,846
- Really?
- Yeah, that's what she told me.

473
00:18:58,929 --> 00:19:01,473
- I'm making the morning announcement.
- Okay.

474
00:19:02,141 --> 00:19:04,726
LAST MORNING ANNOUNCEMENT
CURRENT TIME 8 A.M.

475
00:19:06,353 --> 00:19:08,355
Good morning, everyone.

476
00:19:08,438 --> 00:19:12,109
As you all know, it's our last morning
here at Jae-seok's B&B Rules.

477
00:19:12,192 --> 00:19:15,779
So please take some time to get ready
and join us in the dining area.

478
00:19:15,863 --> 00:19:19,241
We'll be having our last breakfast
here together around 8:30.

479
00:19:19,324 --> 00:19:22,202
Hope you're hungry.
We will see you in a bit.

480
00:19:26,582 --> 00:19:28,625
MOON GOES UP

481
00:19:28,709 --> 00:19:30,460
SUN COMES DOWN

482
00:19:31,044 --> 00:19:33,797
Bryan, why didn't you work out
this morning?

483
00:19:33,881 --> 00:19:35,924
You made it sound
like you work out every morning.

484
00:19:36,008 --> 00:19:37,384
No, I don't.

485
00:19:37,467 --> 00:19:39,970
Hey, Seung-jun, wake up already.

486
00:19:41,013 --> 00:19:42,848
Kwang-chul's already finished packing.

487
00:19:42,931 --> 00:19:44,349
NEAT

488
00:19:45,267 --> 00:19:47,853
ALL PACKED UP
AND MAKING BARLEY TEA

489
00:19:47,936 --> 00:19:49,479
Have some tea, guys.

490
00:19:49,563 --> 00:19:50,898
Oh, yeah, thank you.

491
00:19:50,981 --> 00:19:52,774
- Thank you, <i>hyung</i>.
- Sure.

492
00:19:54,860 --> 00:19:56,904
- Add the meat?
- Yeah, from the start.

493
00:19:56,987 --> 00:19:57,988
WARMING UP THEIR LAST MEAL

494
00:19:58,071 --> 00:20:00,741
Chae-eun,
what was your favorite dish here?

495
00:20:00,824 --> 00:20:03,410
The kimchi fried rice
on the first day was good.

496
00:20:03,493 --> 00:20:05,287
- That's your favorite?
- Yeah, it was the most…

497
00:20:05,370 --> 00:20:06,246
- Seriously?
- Yeah.

498
00:20:06,330 --> 00:20:09,124
- Wow, I'm kind of touched.
- I love kimchi fried rice.

499
00:20:09,208 --> 00:20:11,251
The egg was perfectly runny.

500
00:20:11,335 --> 00:20:12,544
- You liked the eggs?
- Yeah.

501
00:20:12,628 --> 00:20:14,379
Ah, perfect you say…

502
00:20:14,463 --> 00:20:17,090
- Who did the eggs?
- Who else?

503
00:20:17,174 --> 00:20:18,383
PRINCE EGG

504
00:20:18,467 --> 00:20:21,303
What about the soup?
What did you think of the soup that day?

505
00:20:21,386 --> 00:20:22,763
- The pine nut porridge?
- No.

506
00:20:22,846 --> 00:20:25,390
- The doenjang soup? That was good too.
- No, not the doenjang soup.

507
00:20:25,474 --> 00:20:26,975
- Then what?
- You had egg soup too.

508
00:20:27,059 --> 00:20:30,187
- Chae-eun, why can't you remember?
- Oh, right… There was a lot of egg in it.

509
00:20:30,270 --> 00:20:32,856
"There was a lot of egg in it"?
That's not…

510
00:20:32,940 --> 00:20:34,566
- Was it good or…
- Yeah, it was good.

511
00:20:35,150 --> 00:20:36,401
NOT SO CONVINCED

512
00:20:37,903 --> 00:20:40,781
Wait, I should probably wake
Ye-eun up now.

513
00:20:45,744 --> 00:20:48,705
SHE'S NOT ANSWERING THE PHONE?

514
00:20:50,499 --> 00:20:52,584
YE-EUN ISN'T FEELING WELL
AND IS STRUGGLING TO GET UP

515
00:20:52,668 --> 00:20:54,294
I think Ye-eun got a cold.

516
00:20:54,378 --> 00:20:55,379
That could be it.

517
00:20:55,462 --> 00:20:56,964
The temperature did drop so much.

518
00:20:57,047 --> 00:20:58,048
SOME WARM BARLEY TEA

519
00:20:58,131 --> 00:20:59,508
A staff member is sick.

520
00:20:59,591 --> 00:21:01,176
JAE-SEOK GOES TO CHECK ON YE-EUN

521
00:21:04,471 --> 00:21:06,139
Hey, Ye-eun, are you okay?

522
00:21:07,224 --> 00:21:10,560
- I brought you some warm barley tea.
- Okay, thank you.

523
00:21:10,644 --> 00:21:12,562
- Don't get up.
- Okay, thank you.

524
00:21:14,481 --> 00:21:15,315
HAGGARD

525
00:21:15,399 --> 00:21:16,650
Did you take some medicine?

526
00:21:16,733 --> 00:21:20,320
I took my thyroid meds, so I have to wait
about an hour before anything else.

527
00:21:20,404 --> 00:21:21,321
Oh, really?

528
00:21:21,405 --> 00:21:23,699
Hey, you should eat something
before you take the medicine.

529
00:21:23,782 --> 00:21:25,701
Come eat later.
Just get some rest for now.

530
00:21:25,784 --> 00:21:26,827
- Okay.
- Yeah.

531
00:21:26,910 --> 00:21:29,246
- I'll be down soon, give me 15.
- Okay.

532
00:21:30,539 --> 00:21:34,626
Put the radish kimchi here,
next to the kimchi.

533
00:21:34,710 --> 00:21:36,461
Just a little bit here.

534
00:21:36,545 --> 00:21:38,547
ELDEST DAUGHTER ADDS
THE RADISH KIMCHI

535
00:21:39,298 --> 00:21:42,259
SECOND DAUGHTER CARRIES
THE DISHES OUT

536
00:21:42,342 --> 00:21:44,303
Ooh! That looks great.

537
00:21:45,220 --> 00:21:46,221
Wow!

538
00:21:46,305 --> 00:21:47,180
MOUTHWATERING

539
00:21:47,264 --> 00:21:48,348
Wow, nice job.

540
00:21:48,432 --> 00:21:51,435
What would we have done
without Kwang-chul and his family?

541
00:21:51,518 --> 00:21:53,061
We're so glad you're here.

542
00:21:53,145 --> 00:21:56,523
- I'm honored to be here.
- In so many ways, really.

543
00:21:56,606 --> 00:21:59,234
You don't have to go piece by piece.
Just scoop it out.

544
00:21:59,318 --> 00:22:00,444
- You can do that.
- Like this?

545
00:22:00,527 --> 00:22:01,611
Yeah. This is faster.

546
00:22:01,695 --> 00:22:03,363
- Oh, that is better.
- Yeah.

547
00:22:04,156 --> 00:22:05,866
Chae-eun, you're really good at this.

548
00:22:05,949 --> 00:22:07,784
You two must take after your dad.

549
00:22:07,868 --> 00:22:09,119
I don't think I got it from my dad.

550
00:22:09,202 --> 00:22:11,038
Really…
I have no skill for this kind of thing.

551
00:22:11,121 --> 00:22:13,040
Kwang-soo, don't assume
about people's families.

552
00:22:13,123 --> 00:22:15,917
No. That's not what I meant.
You know what I'm trying to say.

553
00:22:16,001 --> 00:22:17,377
Don't be inconsiderate.

554
00:22:17,461 --> 00:22:19,212
- Please wipe down 12 of them.
- Twelve? Okay.

555
00:22:19,296 --> 00:22:20,922
Don't cry today, okay?

556
00:22:21,006 --> 00:22:22,632
Uh-uh. Oh, I didn't cry.

557
00:22:23,133 --> 00:22:25,427
I feel like everyone thinks
I'm a total crybaby now.

558
00:22:25,510 --> 00:22:28,472
- This place is a bit… Well…
- This place is a bit what?

559
00:22:28,555 --> 00:22:30,640
It's strange.
It's a strange kind of place.

560
00:22:30,724 --> 00:22:34,186
- Woo-seok said the same thing.
- I mean, I never cried here…

561
00:22:34,936 --> 00:22:38,023
I never even imagined I would cry.

562
00:22:38,106 --> 00:22:40,567
- Woo-seok's a crier too.
- I've never cried,

563
00:22:40,650 --> 00:22:43,320
but you're right about this being
a strange kind of place.

564
00:22:46,531 --> 00:22:48,033
Oh!

565
00:22:48,742 --> 00:22:52,037
Gomtang really is
the ultimate breakfast classic.

566
00:22:52,746 --> 00:22:53,830
STIRRING THE RICE

567
00:22:53,914 --> 00:22:55,123
Here, look, Chae-won.

568
00:22:55,207 --> 00:22:57,793
When you first make rice,
there's usually more moisture

569
00:22:57,876 --> 00:22:59,169
- at the bottom, right?
- Oh, yeah.

570
00:22:59,252 --> 00:23:01,671
So you mix it up like this to even it out.

571
00:23:01,755 --> 00:23:04,383
- Did you know that?
- She knows that, actually.

572
00:23:04,466 --> 00:23:06,593
- What?
- She knows that part.

573
00:23:06,676 --> 00:23:08,261
You knew?
And you were pretending you didn't?

574
00:23:08,345 --> 00:23:10,597
- You were explaining.
- So sweet.

575
00:23:10,680 --> 00:23:13,183
Chae-won, what am I gonna do with you?

576
00:23:13,266 --> 00:23:15,227
My life goal is to have
a daughter like you.

577
00:23:15,310 --> 00:23:16,603
Whoa!

578
00:23:17,145 --> 00:23:18,480
That's high praise.

579
00:23:18,563 --> 00:23:20,315
I want a husband like you, Kwang-soo.

580
00:23:20,399 --> 00:23:22,609
Oh, stop. You…

581
00:23:22,692 --> 00:23:23,902
I CAN'T WITH HER, SERIOUSLY

582
00:23:23,985 --> 00:23:25,112
What do I say to that?

583
00:23:25,195 --> 00:23:26,196
Oh…

584
00:23:28,115 --> 00:23:29,699
- I want a son like you, Woo-seok.
- Wait…

585
00:23:29,783 --> 00:23:31,451
A son?

586
00:23:31,660 --> 00:23:32,911
MAKES SURE WOO-SEOK
DOESN'T FEEL LEFT OUT

587
00:23:32,994 --> 00:23:35,038
- How long will that take?
- Chae-won.

588
00:23:35,539 --> 00:23:36,665
All right!

589
00:23:37,165 --> 00:23:39,084
Done. Everything's ready.

590
00:23:39,167 --> 00:23:40,794
Let's call everybody in.

591
00:23:41,628 --> 00:23:43,088
Let's eat!

592
00:23:44,423 --> 00:23:45,757
Let's eat!

593
00:23:46,258 --> 00:23:47,509
Let's eat!

594
00:23:47,592 --> 00:23:49,094
- So loud.
- That scared me.

595
00:23:49,469 --> 00:23:50,470
THE DOOR BROTHERS SERVE

596
00:23:50,554 --> 00:23:51,638
- Oh, that's a lot.
- Thank you.

597
00:23:51,721 --> 00:23:53,598
- Please enjoy.
- Wow, that's so much.

598
00:23:53,682 --> 00:23:54,516
Thank you.

599
00:23:54,599 --> 00:23:55,851
How much rice do you want?

600
00:23:55,934 --> 00:23:57,394
A lot, please.

601
00:23:57,477 --> 00:23:58,687
- Ah, of course.
- Yeah.

602
00:23:58,770 --> 00:24:00,689
- A high school senior's got to eat a lot.
- Right.

603
00:24:00,772 --> 00:24:03,316
- Chae-won. Just a little?
- Yes, please.

604
00:24:03,400 --> 00:24:04,609
- How's this? Okay.
- Okay.

605
00:24:04,693 --> 00:24:06,319
Nam-jin, how much?

606
00:24:06,403 --> 00:24:07,654
Bryan, do you want more rice?

607
00:24:07,737 --> 00:24:08,613
Young-gwang.

608
00:24:08,697 --> 00:24:09,656
Seung-hyun, more rice?

609
00:24:09,739 --> 00:24:12,284
Oh, I think that's enough. Thank you.

610
00:24:13,827 --> 00:24:15,412
I got it. I'll get Hye-jeong's.

611
00:24:15,495 --> 00:24:16,830
Thank you.

612
00:24:16,913 --> 00:24:17,956
- Woo-seok.
- Yeah?

613
00:24:18,582 --> 00:24:19,916
Isn't that too much meat?

614
00:24:22,878 --> 00:24:24,421
It's my call.

615
00:24:24,504 --> 00:24:26,006
- Thank you.
- Enjoy.

616
00:24:26,089 --> 00:24:27,174
Okay.

617
00:24:27,507 --> 00:24:28,592
GLANCING

618
00:24:29,176 --> 00:24:30,343
I gave you plenty of meat.

619
00:24:30,427 --> 00:24:32,012
- Oh, thank you. Wow.
- You're my <i>manito</i>.

620
00:24:32,095 --> 00:24:33,722
Oh.

621
00:24:34,473 --> 00:24:35,307
Oh!

622
00:24:35,390 --> 00:24:36,558
(CAN'T LOSE TO HIM)

623
00:24:36,641 --> 00:24:38,059
Wait a minute. <i>Hyung.</i>

624
00:24:38,560 --> 00:24:39,978
I wanna serve Min-ju.

625
00:24:43,190 --> 00:24:44,191
STUNNED BY SUDDEN FLIRTING

626
00:24:44,274 --> 00:24:46,151
- Hi there.
- I'll give you plenty.

627
00:24:46,234 --> 00:24:47,486
Thank you.

628
00:24:50,155 --> 00:24:51,281
Please, enjoy.

629
00:24:51,364 --> 00:24:53,783
Thank you. Thank you.

630
00:24:53,867 --> 00:24:55,785
- Hey, how about some green onion?
- Oh, I…

631
00:24:55,869 --> 00:24:57,537
- Snap out of it.
- Right.

632
00:24:57,621 --> 00:24:59,039
Min-ju, snap out of it.

633
00:24:59,122 --> 00:25:00,415
- Is that enough rice?
- Yeah.

634
00:25:00,499 --> 00:25:01,500
- A little more?
- Yeah.

635
00:25:01,583 --> 00:25:02,667
How's the gomtang?

636
00:25:02,751 --> 00:25:04,127
- It's good. Yeah.
- You like it?

637
00:25:08,298 --> 00:25:09,549
WOW

638
00:25:12,302 --> 00:25:13,428
Mmm.

639
00:25:13,512 --> 00:25:14,888
Gomtang really is the best.

640
00:25:14,971 --> 00:25:16,264
It certainly is.

641
00:25:17,307 --> 00:25:18,308
It's good.

642
00:25:18,391 --> 00:25:19,434
Is it good?

643
00:25:19,518 --> 00:25:21,853
She always does that heart thing. So cute.

644
00:25:21,937 --> 00:25:23,855
Chae-won.

645
00:25:25,690 --> 00:25:27,859
- Good, Ye-eun. Come eat. Have gomtang.
- I'm okay now.

646
00:25:27,943 --> 00:25:29,778
- Are you feeling better?
- Yeah, I got some sleep.

647
00:25:29,861 --> 00:25:31,404
- Have gomtang.
- Okay, I'll have some.

648
00:25:31,488 --> 00:25:33,532
- I was concerned. You want my jacket?
- You're lying.

649
00:25:33,615 --> 00:25:35,408
Seriously, I was worried sick.

650
00:25:35,492 --> 00:25:37,661
- Are you all right?
- Thank you so much.

651
00:25:38,245 --> 00:25:39,579
Aw, it's so warm.

652
00:25:40,372 --> 00:25:43,041
Let's eat. That right there is yours.

653
00:25:45,502 --> 00:25:47,045
Mmm.

654
00:25:47,128 --> 00:25:50,131
You've really been giving us a lot of food
that helps us recharge.

655
00:25:50,215 --> 00:25:51,633
Food that really boosts our energy.

656
00:25:51,716 --> 00:25:53,718
Yesterday was all about loading up
on protein…

657
00:25:53,802 --> 00:25:56,429
You burned so much energy doing
all that wild dancing last night.

658
00:25:56,513 --> 00:25:57,931
Yeah, he's right.

659
00:25:58,014 --> 00:25:59,474
Gomtang's a perfect last meal.

660
00:25:59,558 --> 00:26:00,850
Yeah.

661
00:26:00,934 --> 00:26:02,769
- Even the store owner seemed sad…
- Oh, really?

662
00:26:02,852 --> 00:26:04,020
…that it was our last day.

663
00:26:04,104 --> 00:26:05,939
We've been seeing the folks
at the supermarket

664
00:26:06,022 --> 00:26:07,232
- and all these places so often.
- Right.

665
00:26:07,315 --> 00:26:08,775
SUPERMARKET VISITS: 7
CAFÉ & GOMTANG PLACE: 3

666
00:26:08,858 --> 00:26:12,487
Chae-eun said kimchi fried rice was her
favorite out of everything she had here.

667
00:26:12,571 --> 00:26:14,114
- Oh, really?
- Yeah.

668
00:26:14,197 --> 00:26:15,991
So I told her I made it.

669
00:26:16,074 --> 00:26:17,826
I don't know why you're so happy.

670
00:26:18,785 --> 00:26:20,495
- Didn't we make it together?
- Mm-mmm.

671
00:26:20,579 --> 00:26:21,788
SHAKING HIS HEAD

672
00:26:21,871 --> 00:26:23,873
- Listen, Ye-eun…
- Yeah?

673
00:26:23,957 --> 00:26:26,751
You had some gomtang,
and now you look totally fine.

674
00:26:27,335 --> 00:26:29,546
- I think food really helps. Yeah.
- Right?

675
00:26:29,629 --> 00:26:31,548
Do you have a toothache?

676
00:26:31,631 --> 00:26:34,050
- Why are you holding your cheek?
- Is it a cavity?

677
00:26:34,134 --> 00:26:36,261
- No, it just hurts a bit.
- Oh.

678
00:26:36,845 --> 00:26:38,221
That was good.

679
00:26:38,305 --> 00:26:41,474
Well, you know…
To think this is our last meal here…

680
00:26:41,558 --> 00:26:43,059
Oh, that's true.

681
00:26:45,645 --> 00:26:47,522
What time are we meeting up?

682
00:26:47,606 --> 00:26:51,026
Everyone's almost finished eating, so
I'm thinking around 10:00 should be fine.

683
00:26:55,030 --> 00:26:57,407
TAKING HIS TIME LOOKING
AT EACH GUEST'S FACE

684
00:26:57,490 --> 00:26:59,826
I have to go straight back
to my everyday life.

685
00:27:00,493 --> 00:27:02,829
- You're going back to work tomorrow?
- Yeah.

686
00:27:02,912 --> 00:27:05,624
- So what about training?
- Mine starts tomorrow.

687
00:27:05,707 --> 00:27:07,000
- Right away?
- Yeah.

688
00:27:07,626 --> 00:27:08,877
I have to.

689
00:27:10,879 --> 00:27:13,923
I'll definitely be following you
and rooting for you from now on.

690
00:27:14,007 --> 00:27:15,383
If you compete in a tournament,

691
00:27:15,467 --> 00:27:17,636
I'll be like, "Oh!"
And I'll watch for sure.

692
00:27:17,719 --> 00:27:18,762
Thank you.

693
00:27:19,262 --> 00:27:21,431
So are you going straight back
to work tomorrow?

694
00:27:21,514 --> 00:27:23,350
Yeah, we're going back to work tomorrow.

695
00:27:23,433 --> 00:27:24,684
- Right back to work?
- Yeah.

696
00:27:24,768 --> 00:27:27,270
It's time for us to go back
to the real world.

697
00:27:28,271 --> 00:27:30,523
- Take good care of yourselves.
- Oh, okay.

698
00:27:30,607 --> 00:27:34,027
Seriously, now that I know what you do,
I'm a little worried.

699
00:27:34,110 --> 00:27:35,362
Thank you for saying that.

700
00:27:35,445 --> 00:27:36,821
No, I really mean it.

701
00:27:36,905 --> 00:27:38,365
- Thank you for everything.
- No, thank you.

702
00:27:38,448 --> 00:27:39,449
- Thank you.
- It's been fun.

703
00:27:39,532 --> 00:27:40,533
It's an honor.

704
00:27:40,617 --> 00:27:42,786
WORDS OF ENCOURAGEMENT
TO RETURN TO EVERYDAY LIFE

705
00:27:44,454 --> 00:27:46,915
I don't wanna go home.

706
00:27:46,998 --> 00:27:48,083
Seriously.

707
00:27:48,958 --> 00:27:53,129
Just leave everything here.
We can do the last round of dishes.

708
00:27:53,213 --> 00:27:54,297
- I'll do it. We'll do it.
- It's okay.

709
00:27:54,381 --> 00:27:55,298
- Seriously.
- Just go. Come on.

710
00:27:55,382 --> 00:27:58,968
- Go, go, go. Go get ready. Get ready.
- Seriously, we'll make sure it's clean.

711
00:27:59,052 --> 00:28:01,846
- Thank you.
- Oh, don't even worry about it.

712
00:28:01,930 --> 00:28:03,723
That was a great meal.

713
00:28:03,807 --> 00:28:05,600
THE GUESTS HEAD OFF TO PACK

714
00:28:06,851 --> 00:28:10,772
Yeah, this is a nice way to wrap up.
Just doing the dishes together.

715
00:28:10,855 --> 00:28:12,273
STAFF DOES DISHES ONE LAST TIME

716
00:28:13,108 --> 00:28:14,776
HUDDLED TOGETHER

717
00:28:15,735 --> 00:28:19,072
I MADE WONDERFUL MEMORIES HERE

718
00:28:19,155 --> 00:28:22,242
I'VE BEEN HAPPY
THESE PAST 3 DAYS AND 2 NIGHTS

719
00:28:22,325 --> 00:28:24,035
I really hate to leave.

720
00:28:24,119 --> 00:28:25,370
SEE YOU AGAIN

721
00:28:25,954 --> 00:28:28,331
- Chae-won, you're sad too, right?
- Yeah.

722
00:28:28,915 --> 00:28:31,251
- Bye.
- I've been so happy.

723
00:28:31,334 --> 00:28:35,338
AS THEY POUR THEIR HEARTS
INTO THEIR MESSAGES

724
00:28:36,548 --> 00:28:39,134
THE BOARD QUICKLY FILLS UP
WITH WARMTH

725
00:28:39,926 --> 00:28:40,927
Wanna spin it?

726
00:28:41,428 --> 00:28:43,304
GO HOME - STAY 1 MORE DAY

727
00:28:43,388 --> 00:28:45,306
We're leaving it up to fate.

728
00:28:46,808 --> 00:28:48,351
Hey, it's 50-50.

729
00:28:48,435 --> 00:28:50,311
All right! Oh, no! Good…

730
00:28:50,395 --> 00:28:51,646
- No, no, no, stop.
- …good.

731
00:28:51,730 --> 00:28:53,648
Okay, okay, okay.

732
00:28:53,732 --> 00:28:55,358
All right.

733
00:28:56,151 --> 00:28:59,070
- I should start packing.
- Let's push this back in.

734
00:28:59,779 --> 00:29:01,740
PUSHING THE BED BACK IN

735
00:29:04,284 --> 00:29:07,162
CAREFULLY CAPTURING
THE LAST MOMENTS

736
00:29:07,746 --> 00:29:10,874
THE GYMNASIUM THAT WAS BUSTLING

737
00:29:10,957 --> 00:29:15,253
IS NOW EMPTY

738
00:29:15,336 --> 00:29:17,881
All right, everyone,
please gather over here.

739
00:29:17,964 --> 00:29:20,175
Reminds me of when we first arrived.

740
00:29:20,258 --> 00:29:23,678
- I wish it was re-starting.
- I know. I hate to leave.

741
00:29:23,762 --> 00:29:28,475
All right, everyone. We just had our
orientation the day before yesterday.

742
00:29:28,558 --> 00:29:32,020
Can you believe that it's already time
for us to have the closing ceremony?

743
00:29:32,103 --> 00:29:34,355
I'm really glad
that you stayed safe and healthy

744
00:29:34,439 --> 00:29:37,484
over the course of your stay here
at Jae-seok's B&B Rules.

745
00:29:37,567 --> 00:29:40,236
We don't just do
a regular closing ceremony.

746
00:29:40,320 --> 00:29:43,948
We've taken the time
to choose a few of you as MVPs.

747
00:29:44,032 --> 00:29:47,285
These guests went above and beyond,
and we'll be presenting them awards.

748
00:29:47,368 --> 00:29:48,828
Whoa.

749
00:29:48,912 --> 00:29:50,205
- Who could this be?
- Okay.

750
00:29:50,288 --> 00:29:52,499
The Real-Life Superman Award.

751
00:29:52,582 --> 00:29:54,501
Park Kwang-chul. Congratulations.

752
00:29:55,668 --> 00:29:57,170
"This person dedicated themselves

753
00:29:57,253 --> 00:29:59,380
to ensuring public safety
as a special officer.

754
00:29:59,464 --> 00:30:01,925
At Jae-seok's B&B,
he inspired fathers everywhere

755
00:30:02,008 --> 00:30:05,178
as the role model his eldest daughter
is proud of and emulates.

756
00:30:05,261 --> 00:30:10,141
In recognition, we present this award.
From all of us on staff, congratulations."

757
00:30:14,687 --> 00:30:16,856
LIFTS HIM UP

758
00:30:16,940 --> 00:30:19,067
- Let's give him a round of applause.
- Whoo!

759
00:30:19,150 --> 00:30:20,401
SHAKE IT, SHAKE IT

760
00:30:22,028 --> 00:30:25,073
The Brothers Through Joy and Sorrow Award

761
00:30:25,156 --> 00:30:27,450
goes to Jo Nam-soon and Jo Nam-jin.

762
00:30:27,951 --> 00:30:30,829
"In the sincere hope that the memories
of laughter you shared here

763
00:30:30,912 --> 00:30:33,456
will become a warm source of strength
as you continue on in life,

764
00:30:33,540 --> 00:30:34,916
we present this award."

765
00:30:34,999 --> 00:30:36,876
This is a pretty big award too.

766
00:30:36,960 --> 00:30:38,545
The Woo-seok-Approved Cutie Award

767
00:30:38,628 --> 00:30:40,380
- goes to Park Hye-jeong.
- Oh, gosh.

768
00:30:40,463 --> 00:30:41,506
Thank you.

769
00:30:41,589 --> 00:30:43,591
- So cute!
- At Jae-seok's B&B,

770
00:30:43,675 --> 00:30:45,218
- the above person…
- Nice!

771
00:30:45,301 --> 00:30:49,013
- …was really the only option here.
- No way. That's such a big award.

772
00:30:49,097 --> 00:30:51,766
Congratulations.

773
00:30:51,850 --> 00:30:54,686
- Oh.
- Congratulations once again.

774
00:30:54,769 --> 00:30:55,770
(WHOOSH)

775
00:30:57,438 --> 00:30:58,523
Yeah, well…

776
00:31:01,526 --> 00:31:03,361
Next up is the Gold Medal Award.

777
00:31:03,444 --> 00:31:05,697
Kim Min-ju, Kim I-an and Kim Ha-na.

778
00:31:07,282 --> 00:31:08,867
The Taekwondo Guy Award goes to Bryan.

779
00:31:08,950 --> 00:31:11,661
The Wild Dancer Who Could Outshine
Any Celeb Award

780
00:31:11,744 --> 00:31:13,705
goes to Choi Yeo-won. Congratulations.

781
00:31:13,788 --> 00:31:16,374
All right,
you've all received your awards,

782
00:31:16,457 --> 00:31:19,127
but we've got one more prepared.

783
00:31:19,210 --> 00:31:21,921
I'm really excited about this one.
The Best Comedian Award

784
00:31:22,005 --> 00:31:24,007
goes to Lee Kwang-soo.

785
00:31:28,928 --> 00:31:31,848
"For making us laugh with his body,

786
00:31:32,515 --> 00:31:34,017
with his words,

787
00:31:34,100 --> 00:31:35,184
and even with his face…"

788
00:31:35,268 --> 00:31:36,519
FAILS TO HOLD BACK LAUGHTER

789
00:31:36,603 --> 00:31:38,980
- His face?
- "…and filling this place with joy,

790
00:31:39,063 --> 00:31:41,649
we present this award
to our Best Comedian."

791
00:31:41,733 --> 00:31:44,110
After winning the Best Mosquito Award
with the first group,

792
00:31:44,193 --> 00:31:46,779
this makes him a two-time winner.
Congratulations.

793
00:31:46,863 --> 00:31:47,864
2-TIME WINNER

794
00:31:47,947 --> 00:31:50,408
Thank you so much for growing into
such a great comedian.

795
00:31:50,491 --> 00:31:51,409
- Oh, okay.
- All right.

796
00:31:51,492 --> 00:31:54,495
Isn't he an actor?

797
00:31:54,579 --> 00:31:57,206
All right, how do you feel?
Please share a few words.

798
00:31:57,290 --> 00:31:58,958
Well, time really flies.

799
00:31:59,584 --> 00:32:01,502
Once this moment passes,

800
00:32:01,586 --> 00:32:04,839
<i>Jae-seok's B&B Rules!</i>
will officially be over,

801
00:32:04,923 --> 00:32:08,384
and I just wish I'd been able to
make you feel even more comfortable,

802
00:32:08,468 --> 00:32:09,719
made it even more fun.

803
00:32:09,802 --> 00:32:12,555
You laughed along
with all my cheeky teasing

804
00:32:12,639 --> 00:32:16,309
and all of my silly jokes,
and I really appreciate that.

805
00:32:16,392 --> 00:32:17,226
And yeah,

806
00:32:17,310 --> 00:32:20,563
I just really hope you'll remember
this moment for a long time.

807
00:32:20,647 --> 00:32:25,068
Now it's already time for us to return
to reality from this dream.

808
00:32:25,151 --> 00:32:28,905
Honestly, this place felt like
a dream to me too.

809
00:32:28,988 --> 00:32:32,325
Whenever things get tough out there,
when you're going through a hard time,

810
00:32:32,408 --> 00:32:36,329
I think looking back on this moment,
this dream, will be a great comfort.

811
00:32:37,580 --> 00:32:41,209
Whenever things get hard for me,
I'll remember this moment too.

812
00:32:41,292 --> 00:32:43,836
I had such a wonderful time.
Thank you so much.

813
00:32:45,004 --> 00:32:48,800
I'll be cheering for all of you.
Thank you, all.

814
00:32:52,011 --> 00:32:56,474
That concludes
the official closing ceremony.

815
00:32:56,557 --> 00:33:00,561
Uh, once you leave,
this B&B will be gone too.

816
00:33:01,145 --> 00:33:05,191
Even though it was only three days
and two nights,

817
00:33:05,274 --> 00:33:08,987
I believe the bonds we built
and the feelings we shared

818
00:33:09,070 --> 00:33:12,407
will remain in our memories forever.

819
00:33:12,991 --> 00:33:16,786
When you return to your daily lives
and face difficult times,

820
00:33:17,578 --> 00:33:22,375
I hope your memories here can serve
as a small refuge.

821
00:33:22,458 --> 00:33:26,713
Something that eases your burdens,
even just a little.

822
00:33:27,714 --> 00:33:30,258
In your own lives,
you're all fighting hard,

823
00:33:30,341 --> 00:33:32,844
and sometimes
it can feel like a battlefield.

824
00:33:33,386 --> 00:33:37,306
But rather than exhausting yourself
trying to win every battle,

825
00:33:37,390 --> 00:33:41,436
I hope you'll sometimes focus
simply on surviving.

826
00:33:42,603 --> 00:33:44,522
Comfort yourself

827
00:33:44,605 --> 00:33:49,485
and protect yourself amid that intensity.

828
00:33:50,737 --> 00:33:53,865
I don't think there's
only one right answer in life.

829
00:33:54,365 --> 00:33:56,617
Just live the life you think is right.

830
00:33:56,701 --> 00:33:59,787
The life you believe in.
The life you want for yourself.

831
00:33:59,871 --> 00:34:01,372
Maybe that's the answer.

832
00:34:01,873 --> 00:34:04,208
Don't be shaken by anyone else's opinions.

833
00:34:04,292 --> 00:34:07,003
If you live according to your own will
and your own heart

834
00:34:07,086 --> 00:34:09,005
you can build a happy life for yourself.

835
00:34:10,131 --> 00:34:13,468
I sincerely hope you achieve
everything you wish for.

836
00:34:13,551 --> 00:34:14,969
And please stay healthy.

837
00:34:16,345 --> 00:34:20,641
And with that, we bring
<i>Jae-seok's B&B Rules! </i>to a close.

838
00:34:20,725 --> 00:34:21,726
Thank you.

839
00:34:24,020 --> 00:34:26,647
Aw.

840
00:34:27,440 --> 00:34:28,983
Oh, man, I almost cried.

841
00:34:29,067 --> 00:34:31,903
I'm so sad.

842
00:34:33,905 --> 00:34:36,240
I got a little choked up
when he was talking.

843
00:34:36,324 --> 00:34:38,367
It was touching. I felt grateful too.

844
00:34:38,451 --> 00:34:40,828
When he said, "You're doing just fine,"

845
00:34:40,912 --> 00:34:42,955
I just couldn't hold back my tears.

846
00:34:43,039 --> 00:34:46,876
It really tugged at my heart.
Honestly, I had a lot of emotions.

847
00:34:53,341 --> 00:34:54,926
- Thank you!
- Thank you.

848
00:34:55,009 --> 00:34:57,053
- Thank you all!
- Thank you.

849
00:34:57,136 --> 00:34:58,096
Thank you.

850
00:34:58,721 --> 00:35:01,265
Whoa.

851
00:35:01,349 --> 00:35:02,558
That was touching.

852
00:35:02,642 --> 00:35:05,478
Are you crying?

853
00:35:06,979 --> 00:35:08,022
TEARS FINALLY BURST OUT

854
00:35:08,106 --> 00:35:10,483
Wait, for real? For real?

855
00:35:10,566 --> 00:35:12,401
Why are you crying?

856
00:35:12,485 --> 00:35:13,778
Is it Woo-seok?

857
00:35:13,861 --> 00:35:15,279
It's Woo-seok!

858
00:35:15,363 --> 00:35:17,073
No, it's Yu Jae-seok…

859
00:35:17,156 --> 00:35:20,034
Aw, Chief Yu, your speech made her cry.

860
00:35:20,118 --> 00:35:22,954
- What's wrong, Hye-jeong?
- It made her really sad.

861
00:35:23,037 --> 00:35:24,038
WAAH

862
00:35:24,122 --> 00:35:25,790
She said it was really touching.

863
00:35:25,873 --> 00:35:26,958
NODDING

864
00:35:29,460 --> 00:35:31,254
Oh, it was so touching.

865
00:35:31,921 --> 00:35:34,215
- No, it was touching. The way he said it.
- No, wait a second, <i>unni</i>.

866
00:35:34,298 --> 00:35:36,467
You just said the other day,
you weren't going to cry.

867
00:35:36,551 --> 00:35:38,678
Whatever. I can't help it.

868
00:35:38,761 --> 00:35:40,680
- Aw.
- Don't get sick, <i>unni</i>.

869
00:35:40,763 --> 00:35:42,056
Seriously, don't get sick.

870
00:35:42,140 --> 00:35:45,393
Thank you for everything.
You really made me feel comfortable here.

871
00:35:45,476 --> 00:35:47,228
- Kwang-soo, thank you so much.
- Oh, come on.

872
00:35:47,311 --> 00:35:48,729
GOODBYE LEE-JOONG,
A SPECIAL (?) BOND

873
00:35:48,813 --> 00:35:50,398
- Good luck with work.
- I appreciate you.

874
00:35:50,481 --> 00:35:51,983
- Oh, same here.
- Thank you.

875
00:35:52,066 --> 00:35:54,277
- Thank you for everything.
- Oh, thank you.

876
00:35:54,360 --> 00:35:56,445
Your hands… I can feel the power.

877
00:35:56,529 --> 00:35:59,866
Wow, that's so cool.
You've got the coolest hands, seriously.

878
00:35:59,949 --> 00:36:02,118
- So do you. Your hands are so cool.
- No, seriously.

879
00:36:02,201 --> 00:36:04,495
- Take care, Young-gwang. Good luck.
- Thank you for everything.

880
00:36:04,579 --> 00:36:06,414
- I'll be rooting for you.
- Stay healthy.

881
00:36:08,166 --> 00:36:09,959
- Thank you.
- Thanks for everything.

882
00:36:11,377 --> 00:36:12,879
- Bye, Seung-jun.
- Bye.

883
00:36:15,256 --> 00:36:16,257
Take care of yourself.

884
00:36:16,340 --> 00:36:18,301
This has been the happiest time
of my life.

885
00:36:18,384 --> 00:36:20,219
- Really?
- Yes.

886
00:36:21,762 --> 00:36:24,098
- Even happier than my birthday.
- You really mean that?

887
00:36:24,182 --> 00:36:25,391
Before Chae-won left,

888
00:36:25,474 --> 00:36:28,477
she said, "This has been
the happiest time of my life."

889
00:36:28,561 --> 00:36:30,563
Is there a better compliment than that?

890
00:36:31,063 --> 00:36:33,316
Oh, I'm so happy to hear that.

891
00:36:34,233 --> 00:36:35,610
- Hold on, are you crying?
- No.

892
00:36:35,693 --> 00:36:38,029
I was touched
by Jae-seok's speech earlier.

893
00:36:38,112 --> 00:36:40,072
His voice does have a certain magic to it.

894
00:36:40,156 --> 00:36:41,657
Yeah, exactly.

895
00:36:41,741 --> 00:36:45,620
You know, I'm not really the type to cry,
but I got choked up a lot here.

896
00:36:45,703 --> 00:36:47,038
Yeah, me too. Me too.

897
00:36:47,663 --> 00:36:49,081
It's hot.

898
00:36:49,165 --> 00:36:51,626
We'll be going now!
Thank you for everything!

899
00:36:51,709 --> 00:36:53,002
- Bye now.
- Thank you!

900
00:36:53,085 --> 00:36:54,128
- Nam-jin, you too.
- Bye!

901
00:36:54,212 --> 00:36:55,379
Bye!

902
00:36:56,881 --> 00:36:58,174
See you.

903
00:36:58,257 --> 00:37:00,092
Goodbye.

904
00:37:00,176 --> 00:37:03,679
I got so emotional listening
to him. It was kind of healing.

905
00:37:03,763 --> 00:37:04,847
I know.

906
00:37:05,806 --> 00:37:08,559
- This feels weird.
- Can't believe we're leaving.

907
00:37:09,060 --> 00:37:11,437
It's so hard to leave.

908
00:37:11,520 --> 00:37:13,773
No… Bye.

909
00:37:13,856 --> 00:37:16,692
- See you later.
- Goodbye, everyone!

910
00:37:18,986 --> 00:37:20,821
I haven't really had many chances

911
00:37:20,905 --> 00:37:24,033
to focus just on myself
or the four of us like this.

912
00:37:24,116 --> 00:37:28,663
And during my time here, my worries
and concerns didn't cross my mind at all.

913
00:37:28,746 --> 00:37:32,708
It felt like I could finally
just be myself.

914
00:37:32,792 --> 00:37:34,752
I think that was the moment I realized

915
00:37:34,835 --> 00:37:36,837
I had found the answers I was looking for.

916
00:37:36,921 --> 00:37:38,047
Throughout this process,

917
00:37:38,130 --> 00:37:41,342
we were just seeing each other
for who we are, without any prejudice.

918
00:37:41,425 --> 00:37:43,261
It felt like everyone could be themselves.

919
00:37:43,344 --> 00:37:45,054
Like, you do you and I'll do me.

920
00:37:45,137 --> 00:37:47,848
I was like, "Can we really be this happy?"

921
00:37:48,432 --> 00:37:51,310
Playing games together,
teasing each other,

922
00:37:51,394 --> 00:37:53,229
pulling little pranks like that…

923
00:37:53,312 --> 00:37:55,564
I really enjoyed those moments too.

924
00:37:56,649 --> 00:38:01,779
It was one of the few moments in my life
that really felt like magic.

925
00:38:01,862 --> 00:38:04,490
Here, I wasn't a mother
or someone's daughter.

926
00:38:04,573 --> 00:38:06,492
I was just me, Hyeong-seon.

927
00:38:06,575 --> 00:38:09,495
It was a liberating space
where I could be myself.

928
00:38:11,247 --> 00:38:13,165
A glimpse of heaven.

929
00:38:13,833 --> 00:38:16,210
You get hurt and disappointed
by people all the time.

930
00:38:16,294 --> 00:38:18,212
But at least in this space,

931
00:38:18,296 --> 00:38:22,341
it felt like everyone was truly worthy
of respect and love.

932
00:38:22,425 --> 00:38:25,845
It felt so unreal,
but then it was so warm.

933
00:38:25,928 --> 00:38:29,432
And at the same time,
it felt like my own life.

934
00:38:30,057 --> 00:38:33,561
All of that combined made me think,
"Wait, is this a dream?"

935
00:38:34,437 --> 00:38:37,273
I definitely feel
that I've been recharged,

936
00:38:37,356 --> 00:38:39,984
like I can go back
and work even harder now.

937
00:38:40,067 --> 00:38:42,820
I thought, "I'm going to go
back home and live like a king."

938
00:38:42,903 --> 00:38:45,239
I'm gonna hold this dream
close to my heart

939
00:38:45,323 --> 00:38:50,703
and use that strength to motivate myself
and keep going in my daily life.

940
00:38:50,786 --> 00:38:56,792
JAE-SEOK'S B&B

941
00:38:59,920 --> 00:39:01,630
JUST THE FOUR OF THEM LEFT
AT THE B&B

942
00:39:01,714 --> 00:39:04,008
Wow, I can't believe
this day's finally here.

943
00:39:04,550 --> 00:39:05,926
I know.

944
00:39:06,010 --> 00:39:08,346
Wow, I can't believe
this day has finally come.

945
00:39:10,806 --> 00:39:14,769
BY THE WATERFALL
WHERE LAUGHTER NEVER STOPPED

946
00:39:16,020 --> 00:39:18,814
We're closing up now. We're all done.

947
00:39:18,898 --> 00:39:21,692
Wow, this is the end. It's really the end.

948
00:39:21,776 --> 00:39:23,027
SEEING THE QUIET,
IT FINALLY SINKS IN

949
00:39:23,110 --> 00:39:24,487
- One, two, three. Bam!
- Two, three. Bam!

950
00:39:24,570 --> 00:39:26,489
That's it. That's it. You got it.

951
00:39:27,531 --> 00:39:29,367
Yeah, I went backpacking
with a friend on a whim.

952
00:39:29,450 --> 00:39:30,284
Really?

953
00:39:30,368 --> 00:39:31,744
SNACK BAR
ONCE BUSTLING WITH GUESTS

954
00:39:31,827 --> 00:39:33,996
This place has really felt
like my own home!

955
00:39:34,080 --> 00:39:35,623
IS NOW BACK TO HOW IT WAS
ON DAY ONE

956
00:39:35,706 --> 00:39:37,750
We're saying goodbye to this place too.

957
00:39:37,833 --> 00:39:38,709
Seriously.

958
00:39:38,793 --> 00:39:40,169
DINING AREA
WHERE THEY SPENT THE MOST TIME

959
00:39:43,214 --> 00:39:47,218
If it had just been us,
we probably couldn't have done this.

960
00:39:47,301 --> 00:39:49,011
All the guests helped us out.

961
00:39:49,595 --> 00:39:52,139
And I'm really grateful for that.

962
00:39:52,681 --> 00:39:53,891
Man.

963
00:39:55,059 --> 00:39:56,477
We all worked really hard.

964
00:39:56,560 --> 00:39:57,686
We really did.

965
00:39:58,312 --> 00:40:00,314
And that's why it's hard to see it end.

966
00:40:00,398 --> 00:40:01,482
- That's right.
- Yeah, you're right.

967
00:40:01,565 --> 00:40:03,317
If you don't give it your all,
you don't feel this way.

968
00:40:03,401 --> 00:40:04,318
- You're right.
- Exactly.

969
00:40:08,864 --> 00:40:11,575
- Only our shoes are left.
- That's crazy.

970
00:40:11,659 --> 00:40:14,870
- Wow.
- Wow. No way.

971
00:40:16,247 --> 00:40:17,081
Ah!

972
00:40:17,164 --> 00:40:19,667
Check it out!
They wrote messages for us here.

973
00:40:19,750 --> 00:40:20,918
- Really?
- Yeah.

974
00:40:21,001 --> 00:40:22,128
"I've been happy."

975
00:40:22,211 --> 00:40:25,089
Before Chae-won left, she said
this was the happiest time she's had

976
00:40:25,172 --> 00:40:27,133
- in her whole life.
- She said it was the happiest time.

977
00:40:27,216 --> 00:40:30,136
- Even happier than her birthday.
- Really? That's so cute.

978
00:40:30,219 --> 00:40:32,471
Lee-joong wrote that the food was good.

979
00:40:32,555 --> 00:40:35,474
"Thank you for giving my family
such unforgettable memories.

980
00:40:35,558 --> 00:40:37,393
Unbreakable Kwang-chul."

981
00:40:37,893 --> 00:40:40,479
A SPACE THAT WILL SOON BE GONE

982
00:40:41,063 --> 00:40:42,940
Hey, you know what? This is kind of fun.

983
00:40:43,441 --> 00:40:44,859
Ah, this is nice.

984
00:40:44,942 --> 00:40:46,777
Yeah, they were all so thoughtful.

985
00:40:46,861 --> 00:40:49,113
<i>Yodel-ay, yodel-ay, yodel-ay-hee-ee </i>

986
00:40:49,196 --> 00:40:50,823
IT'S WHERE THEY LAUGHED, TALKED,

987
00:40:50,906 --> 00:40:53,033
AND MESSED AROUND
TO THEIR HEARTS' CONTENT

988
00:40:53,117 --> 00:40:56,829
It really feels like everything
just swept through like a storm.

989
00:40:57,496 --> 00:40:58,581
Whoa.

990
00:41:01,125 --> 00:41:03,085
Let's pack up our things and head out.

991
00:41:03,544 --> 00:41:04,670
SAD

992
00:41:06,964 --> 00:41:08,299
Great work, everyone.

993
00:41:08,382 --> 00:41:09,967
LAST LIGHTS-OUT
AT JAE-SEOK'S B&B

994
00:41:10,050 --> 00:41:11,135
It's time.

995
00:41:11,218 --> 00:41:12,678
Let's pack up our stuff.

996
00:41:16,098 --> 00:41:18,642
CHIEF YU CAPTURES A FEW
LAST MEMORIES BEFORE LEAVING

997
00:41:36,118 --> 00:41:37,995
It's really over now, isn't it?

998
00:41:39,246 --> 00:41:41,665
PACKING UP MAKES IT FINALLY
SINK IN THAT IT'S OVER

999
00:41:41,749 --> 00:41:43,042
It was fun.

1000
00:41:43,626 --> 00:41:45,544
It was a relaxing retreat.

1001
00:41:45,628 --> 00:41:47,963
We're not happy all the time, are we?

1002
00:41:48,047 --> 00:41:50,466
Those happy moments
only come once in a while,

1003
00:41:50,549 --> 00:41:52,801
and there are tough times too.

1004
00:41:52,885 --> 00:41:55,721
So I just hope that
when people think back on this

1005
00:41:55,804 --> 00:41:58,140
and think, "Yeah, those were good times,"

1006
00:41:58,224 --> 00:42:01,227
it helps them forget
about whatever they're dealing with,

1007
00:42:01,310 --> 00:42:03,270
even for a little while.

1008
00:42:03,354 --> 00:42:06,106
Well, don't get sick. No getting sick.

1009
00:42:06,649 --> 00:42:09,276
I feel like I've made
really meaningful memories here.

1010
00:42:09,360 --> 00:42:12,029
Something I can draw strength from
when things get hard.

1011
00:42:12,112 --> 00:42:14,156
It makes me happy,
and I'm proud of myself.

1012
00:42:14,240 --> 00:42:16,575
I kept thinking, "If not for this show,

1013
00:42:16,659 --> 00:42:19,870
when else would I ever get to experience
something like this?"

1014
00:42:19,954 --> 00:42:21,622
It really felt like a gift.

1015
00:42:22,164 --> 00:42:24,208
I thought, "I'm so glad I did this.

1016
00:42:24,291 --> 00:42:27,336
I guess there really is a kind of joy
I can bring to these people."

1017
00:42:27,419 --> 00:42:31,882
This B&B has been
such a great joy for me. Yeah.

1018
00:42:32,508 --> 00:42:35,135
It made me realize,
"So this is what makes a B&B fun."

1019
00:42:35,219 --> 00:42:36,804
7:00 a.m.!

1020
00:42:36,887 --> 00:42:41,892
"The real joy is in being together.
That's the greatest joy of all."

1021
00:42:43,185 --> 00:42:46,647
In a B&B like this
with so many different guests,

1022
00:42:46,730 --> 00:42:49,733
I don't know what their lives
have been like up until now,

1023
00:42:49,817 --> 00:42:51,443
- what they do for a living…
- Welcome!

1024
00:42:51,527 --> 00:42:52,987
…or what's been on their minds,

1025
00:42:53,070 --> 00:42:57,366
but at least while they're here,
I hope they can forget all of that.

1026
00:42:57,449 --> 00:43:00,578
I wanted this B&B to be a place
where you could just be happy

1027
00:43:00,661 --> 00:43:01,662
and enjoy yourself.

1028
00:43:02,454 --> 00:43:03,497
And more than anything,

1029
00:43:03,581 --> 00:43:06,709
I hoped that when they went back
to their own lives,

1030
00:43:06,792 --> 00:43:10,921
this would be a place that came to mind
whenever things got hard or felt dull.

1031
00:43:11,005 --> 00:43:13,299
And I think it really turned out that way.

1032
00:43:13,382 --> 00:43:17,011
They talked nonstop, played hard,
and messed around all they wanted.

1033
00:43:17,094 --> 00:43:19,638
Despite having different jobs
and different lives,

1034
00:43:19,722 --> 00:43:23,017
just seeing them have fun together
like that makes me feel like

1035
00:43:23,100 --> 00:43:26,604
we more than accomplished the goal
we talked about at the beginning.

1036
00:43:34,528 --> 00:43:35,529
You did great.

1037
00:43:35,613 --> 00:43:37,323
- Even you did a good job.
- Great work, everyone.

1038
00:43:37,406 --> 00:43:39,700
- I was really focused this time.
- Right.

1039
00:43:39,783 --> 00:43:42,161
I asked for a time each day
to read my script.

1040
00:43:42,244 --> 00:43:45,247
Yeah, I know. You did.
But you never brought it up again.

1041
00:43:45,331 --> 00:43:47,750
I tried day one…

1042
00:43:47,833 --> 00:43:49,877
…but there's no way I can read here.

1043
00:43:49,960 --> 00:43:52,379
- I'd just be faking.
- Right.

1044
00:43:52,963 --> 00:43:54,798
Honestly, it was pretty hard for me.

1045
00:43:55,507 --> 00:43:57,718
What if we do a second season,

1046
00:43:57,801 --> 00:44:00,554
but we replace you with someone else?

1047
00:44:00,638 --> 00:44:01,722
You'd be hurt.

1048
00:44:01,805 --> 00:44:02,806
If that happened?

1049
00:44:02,890 --> 00:44:03,932
- Yeah.
- Be honest.

1050
00:44:08,103 --> 00:44:09,521
CHIEF YU'S ANXIOUS

1051
00:44:09,605 --> 00:44:10,564
Come on, be honest.

1052
00:44:11,273 --> 00:44:12,691
You'd be hurt if we didn't tell you right?

1053
00:44:12,775 --> 00:44:15,069
- Without telling him?
- You'd be upset too.

1054
00:44:15,152 --> 00:44:16,195
That would cross a line.

1055
00:44:19,490 --> 00:44:20,491
Too honest?

1056
00:44:20,574 --> 00:44:21,909
TRUE FEELINGS SPILLED OUT

1057
00:44:21,992 --> 00:44:24,411
I mean… Seriously, you've got to tell me.

1058
00:44:24,495 --> 00:44:26,455
- Right? I thought so.
- See? You'd be hurt.

1059
00:44:26,538 --> 00:44:28,457
- That's what happens.
- You would.

1060
00:44:28,874 --> 00:44:30,250
FALLEN FOR THE CHARM OF THE B&B

1061
00:44:30,334 --> 00:44:31,877
That was funny.

1062
00:44:31,960 --> 00:44:32,878
Good job, everyone.

1063
00:44:32,961 --> 00:44:35,673
WE DID GREAT

1064
00:44:35,756 --> 00:44:38,342
I haven't done this in so long. Seriously.

1065
00:44:38,425 --> 00:44:39,301
All right!

1066
00:44:39,385 --> 00:44:41,261
Everyone, attention!

1067
00:44:41,345 --> 00:44:42,721
Bye!

1068
00:44:42,805 --> 00:44:44,807
Bye!

1069
00:44:47,559 --> 00:44:50,187
- "Attention"? Really?
- That was a bit…

1070
00:44:50,270 --> 00:44:51,480
"Attention."

1071
00:44:51,563 --> 00:44:53,440
Why did you say that?
We're just saying bye.

1072
00:44:53,524 --> 00:44:54,733
- Shut up.
- What?

1073
00:44:55,818 --> 00:44:56,860
I said shut up.

1074
00:44:59,363 --> 00:45:02,449
THE GUEST IS KING, AND SO AM I
CHIEF YU AND STAFF-

1075
00:45:09,289 --> 00:45:11,709
You know…

1076
00:45:11,792 --> 00:45:15,170
…when the production team reached out,
we started talking about different ideas.

1077
00:45:15,254 --> 00:45:17,881
- But I had to think about it, right?
- Right.

1078
00:45:17,965 --> 00:45:19,925
So I was thinking about it,

1079
00:45:20,008 --> 00:45:23,554
and then they asked me
what kind of place I wanted it to be.

1080
00:45:23,637 --> 00:45:25,139
- Oh.
- And I was like,

1081
00:45:25,764 --> 00:45:27,599
- "What kind of place?"
- Mm-hmm.

1082
00:45:27,683 --> 00:45:30,185
And then it suddenly hit me.

1083
00:45:31,019 --> 00:45:34,231
A place that exists in your imagination,

1084
00:45:34,314 --> 00:45:37,818
- but you can't actually find in real life.
- I see. Mm-hmm.

1085
00:45:37,901 --> 00:45:40,446
Like something that disappears
when you wake up from a dream

1086
00:45:40,529 --> 00:45:42,406
or snap back to reality.
That kind of place.

1087
00:45:42,489 --> 00:45:44,324
Like a place where you stay
for a few days,

1088
00:45:44,408 --> 00:45:46,869
and once you go home,
it feels like it's just gone?

1089
00:45:46,952 --> 00:45:48,912
- Even though it did happen.
- Exactly.

1090
00:45:48,996 --> 00:45:51,540
And people who weren't there with you

1091
00:45:51,623 --> 00:45:54,084
- wouldn't know what it was like.
- Right, they wouldn't get it.

1092
00:45:54,168 --> 00:45:58,005
That's the kind of place I had in mind,
and I vaguely described it.

1093
00:45:58,672 --> 00:46:00,966
But then I realized today
that this is really that kind of place,

1094
00:46:01,049 --> 00:46:02,885
- just like you said. Yeah.
- They're enjoying it.

1095
00:46:02,968 --> 00:46:05,012
- It feels like a dream.
- It does.

1096
00:46:05,095 --> 00:46:08,265
- This whole thing has felt like a movie.
- Wow. You're right.

1097
00:46:09,725 --> 00:46:10,726
We're done.

1098
00:46:11,977 --> 00:46:13,812
That's really spot on, by the way.

1099
00:46:14,313 --> 00:46:17,775
"The guest is king, and so am I."
Right now, we're the kings.

1100
00:46:17,858 --> 00:46:19,902
- We are, right.
- The guests are working for us.

1101
00:46:19,985 --> 00:46:21,111
- Exactly.
- That's true.

1102
00:46:21,195 --> 00:46:22,488
Right?

1103
00:46:22,571 --> 00:46:23,781
Wow, this is…

1104
00:46:23,864 --> 00:46:26,200
- Wow.
- It was just an idea at first…

1105
00:46:26,283 --> 00:46:28,577
- That's how it ended up.
- This has all been perfect.

1106
00:46:28,660 --> 00:46:30,120
Just perfect.
